CPC Corp.,  Taiwan ’s state oil
refiner, seeks to import 22,000 metric tons of liquefied
petroleum gas in April, the Taipei-based company said on its
website today.  Details of the company’s planned purchase are as follows:       LPG, a by-product of oil refining and crude and natural gas
output, is used for cooking, heating and as a motor fuel in  Asia .  To contact the reporter on the story: Yu-huay Sun in Taipei at
